Stigma from patients seeking treatment at Kitui Level 4 Referral Hospital has gone down following the introduction of two separate customer service desks. Initially, male patients would bulldoze their way at the expense of female patients. Some patients, especially those with acute terminal diseases, would not open up for fear of who might be listening. Governor Charity Ngilu on Sunday said some patients who needed emergency treatment would end up waiting longer than they should have for treatment. “This is just but a step in ensuring patients don't feel neglected. It’s part of therapy,” she said.    